               <msContents>
                  <summary>This copy begins with a memorandum at the margins of folioمحسن فانی گوید</summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="Persian_MS_189-item1">
                     <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_2250">Dabistān</title>
                     <title xml:lang="ar-Latn-x-lc" type="alt" key="work_2250">Tabṣirat al-maz̲āhib va taẕkira al-adyān</title>
                     <title xml:lang="ar" key="work_2250">دبستان</title>
                     <title xml:lang="ar" type="alt" key="work_2250">تبصرت المذاهب و تذکرت الادیان</title>
                     <title xml:lang="ar" type="alt" key="work_2250">Dabistān al-maẕāhib</title>
                     <title xml:lang="fa" type="alt" key="work_2250">Dabistān-i maẕāhib</title>
                     <incipit xml:lang="ar" type="basmalla">بسم الله الرحمان الرحیم , ای نام تو سر دفتر اطفال دبستان, یاد ببالغ نظران شمع شبستان</incipit>
                     <explicit xml:lang="ar"/>
                     <listBibl>
                        <bibl>In a MS. note in this copy, Lewin seems to agree with Sir W. Ouseley’s (Travels iii, 564) in ascribing the work to Mubid Shah. He speaks of Muhsin Fani, to whom the work was previously ascribed, as only the "poet quoted at the beginning". This copy begins with a memorandum at the margin of page 1: Muhsin Fani says محسن فانی گوید which may only refer to the verses and prove nothing. Rieu describes a copy of this work ascribed to Shaykh Muḥsin Fanī Kashmīrī (Rieu, BM 142a-b). Another copy of this work (in a collection in Tehran University, No. 4389, vol xiii, p 3352) is ascribed to Shaykh Muḥammad Muḥsin Fanī Kashmīrī or Mullā Mūbid Shāh: از شیخ محمد محسن فانی کشمیری یا ملا موبد شاه</bibl>
                        <bibl type="related-text">another copy of <idno>Persian MS 75</idno>
                        </bibl>
                     </listBibl>
                     <textLang mainLang="fa">Persian</textLang>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
