                        <desc>Black ink ; rubrics in read ; stylish nasta‘līq mixed with shikastah</desc> Copied by <persName key="person_f1839">Kashi Nathah</persName> (?), a Brahman from city of Sialkot in Punjab, on the <date calendar="#Hijri-qamari" when="1796">15th Ramazan 1210</date> نسخه دبستان مذاهب بخط بنده کاشی ناتهه (؟) قوم بر همن متوطن ملک پنجاب بلده سیالکوت تحریر پذیرفت پانزدهم شهر رمضان المبارک سنه 1210 هجری .</handNote>
                  </handDesc>
                  <additions>
                     <list>
                        <item>
                           <label>Bookplates</label> Bibilotheca Lindesiana, Bland MSS No. 410</item>
                        <item>
                           <label>Marginalia</label> A note penciled on the <locus>fly leaf</locus> suggests that it previously belonged to library of the Governor <persName ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/19247044/" key="person_f1771">Jonathan Duncan, 1756-1811</persName>
                        </item>
                        <item>
                           <label>Marginalia</label> Some explanatory notes in English by <persName key="person_f2018">Lewin</persName>, who seems to agree with <name ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/18419237">Sir William Ouseley, 1767-1842</name>'s <title>Travels in Arabia</title> (iii, 564) in ascribing the work to <persName key="person_f3087">Mūbid Shāh</persName>. He speaks of <persName ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/47114320" key="person_f2909">Muḥsin Fānī, -1671 or 1672</persName> to whom the work was previously ascribed as only the "poet quoted at the beginning".</item>
                     </list>
                     <catchwords>Catchwords on every verso page</catchwords>
                  </additions>
